woody: predict wood occurrence data based on discharge data

Lise Vaudor

2021-12-22

woody.Rmd

Prepare data

mypath="../data-raw/mem_data/woody_data_train/"
mystation="V2942010"
fs::dir_tree(mypath)
#> ../data-raw/mem_data/woody_data_train/
#> ├── event_1
#> │   ├── Wood Log 20071123 09h56m.txt
#> │   ├── Wood Log 20071123 10h11m.txt
#> │   ├── Wood Log 20071123 10h56m.txt
#> │   ├── Wood Log 20071123 11h56m.txt
#> │   └── Wood Log 20071123 12h56m.txt
#> └── event_2
#>     ├── Wood Log 20071123 13h56m.txt
#>     ├── Wood Log 20071123 14h26m.txt
#>     ├── Wood Log 20071123 14h56m.txt
#>     ├── Wood Log 20071123 15h56m.txt
#>     └── Wood Log 20071123 16h50m.txt
library(woody)
#> Le chargement a nécessité le package : randomForest
#> randomForest 4.6-14
#> Type rfNews() to see new features/changes/bug fixes.

Import all wood log files inside a file (1 directory per event)

Wdat=import_Wdata(mypath,site="training")

Collect qtvar data from banquehydro, for the period covered by Wdata

Qdat=get_Qdata(Wdata=Wdat,
               station=mystation,
               back_in_time=TRUE)
#> [1] "Collecting QTVAR data between times t1=23/11/2007 08:37 and t2=23/11/2007 16:25."
#> [1] "Collecting QTVAR data between times t1=23/11/2006 08:37 and t2=23/11/2007 08:37."

Qdat %>% 
  dplyr::pull(Time) %>% 
  range()
#> [1] "2006-11-23 08:37:00 UTC" "2007-11-23 16:25:00 UTC"

head(Qdat)

Qdatc=complete_Qdata(qtvar=Qdat,site="site1")

Complete Wdat with discharge data (interpolating Qdat)

Wdatc=complete_Wdata_with_Qdata(Wdata=Wdat,
                                Qdata=Qdatc)
head(Wdatc)

#> 6 training even… trainin… 2007-11-23 08:57:30 2007-11-23  417.  135.  2.00  11.6

Then calculate Wdata_wt, where 1 row= 1 waiting time between two wood occurrences.

Wdat_wt=Wdata_as_waiting_times(Wdatc)

Run random forest

myrf <- run_rf(Wdat_wt)
myrf
#> 
#> Call:
#>  randomForest(formula = Y ~ ., data = Wdata_rf) 
#>                Type of random forest: regression
#>                      Number of trees: 500
#> No. of variables tried at each split: 1
#> 
#>           Mean of squared residuals: 1.262313
#>                     % Var explained: -15.4

Predict on training data itself

Wdat_wt=predict_rf(obj_rf=myrf,
                   newdata=Wdat_wt)

R2:

calc_rf_R2(Wdat_wt)
#> # A tibble: 1 × 3
#>     SCR   SCT    R2
#>   <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
#> 1  796. 2273. 0.650

Get predictions on another dataset

pathpred="../data-raw/mem_data/woody_data_predict/"

Wdat_forpred=import_Wdata(pathpred)

Qdat_forpred= get_Qdata(Wdat_forpred, station="V2942010") %>% 
    complete_Qdata()
#> [1] "Collecting QTVAR data between times t1=12/04/2008 16:46 and t2=13/04/2008 11:40."
#> [1] "Collecting QTVAR data between times t1=12/04/2007 16:46 and t2=12/04/2008 16:46."

Wdat_pred=Wdat_forpred %>%
  complete_Wdata_with_Qdata(Qdat_forpred) %>% 
  Wdata_as_waiting_times() 

pred_rf=predict_rf(Wdat_pred,myrf)
calc_rf_R2(pred_rf)
#> # A tibble: 1 × 3
#>     SCR   SCT    R2
#>   <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
#> 1  452.  154. -1.93
